SKILL ROUTING: User directed -> `deep-research`; proceeding read-only with capped inventory search.
The initial inventory confirms the audit’s named files and shows wrapper call sites in three handlers; I’m reading the delete implementations/callers plus the phase spec to distinguish direct SQL from routed deletes.
The phase spec already contains the 2026-06-05 rescope note and the naming note, but its scope list still misses some now-confirmed files and still carries CocoIndex research-basis lines.
`handlers/memory-health.ts` in the spec is stale; the live file is `handlers/memory-crud-health.ts`, where `autoRepair` invokes `cleanupOrphanedEdges()`.
A wider live-code search adds one non-handler live caller outside the requested dirs: `mcp_server/cli.ts` invokes `deleteEdgesForMemory`; test-only deletes are not production delete sites.
